reviews.review:
First: the movie is way better that The Last Jedi!
It is really fun to watch and as a Star Wars fan you will enjoy it. 
My advice: watch it as the little kid who just saw Star Wars for the first time not as the a Hardcore fan who can name every Sith that ever lived. 
It is by no means perfect and that is more than okay, the prequels were not either and I still enjoyed them. I had a very bad feeling about this movie but I was very pleasantly surprised and I regained my hope; Star Wars is not lost, the battle continues. 
Jokes aside. The pacing of this movie is very fast there are not 5 minutes you can take a breath, it is packed with plot or stuff that happens. That is good and bad. I got the feeling JJ tried to fit 3 movies into 1. And I bet it could have been easily 1 hour longer. There are some corny scenes but not bad ones. But there are many very good scenes! Because there is so much happening many convenient things happen to glue the plot together but I do not really mind as it keeps everything going. Considering JJ had to repair the mess TLJ left behind and end the whole saga he did an incredible job. 
Do not listen too much to these professional critics and enjoy a good and fun Star Wars movie!
Tldr: 0 to 100 real quick, fun movie. Watch as the kid you were when you discovered Star Wars not as the hardcore Fan. Just enjoy it!

Realmente um dos melhores da saga
Claro tem pontos negativos, mas é um ótimo filme, encerra a saga com sucesso e INCRÍVELMENTE

A wonky, bloated film that feels like director JJ Abrams was trying to fit his Episode 8 and 9 into a single film. This movie bites off more than it can chew. It's practical effects and locations were fantastic, but unexplored. The score is perfect, in every sense of the word and carries the film at every beat. There were truly some funny and heartfelt moments, but they were weighed down by recycled plot points and uninspired action. It's not Game of Thrones bad, but it's not Endgame good. It lies somewhere in the middle.
Sure, it's a little chaotic in moments, and crams an awful lot in, but I love it. LOVE IT!!
muy buena pelicula, para terminar la saga de una exelente manera, los que no les gusta solo lo dicen porque no les gusta Disney, no es la mejor pero de esta trilogía seguro lo es
I'VE NEVER LAUGHED SO HARD AT A MOVIE. Yes Disney I'm laughing AT you.

I don't know why I expected more than what we got from the last two episodes.
INSTA Jedi Mary Sue Rey and the rest of the bumbling characters are stuck in a loop of nothing really until the end which was actually more predictable than expected and pretty dumb. Basically the Force is a participation trophy now, a lot of scenes didn't make any relevant point or help the story move along much like The last Jedi garbage.
